13:27.333 --> 13:28.200
No.

13:28.200 --> 13:29.700
No, it's not.

13:30.700 --> 13:33.766
The point, Erica,
is for you, ultimately,

13:33.766 --> 13:36.066
to do all of this
on your own.

13:36.066 --> 13:38.500
And if you honestly see
what we do in here

13:38.500 --> 13:39.700
as the solution,

13:39.700 --> 13:42.633
then... well,
I'm failing.

13:43.633 --> 13:45.133
Dr. Tom...

13:45.133 --> 13:49.500
Think it might be time
to rip away the safety net.

13:49.500 --> 13:53.766
Erica, today you're gonna
solve your problems

13:53.766 --> 13:57.500
like the other 6 billion
souls on this planet:

13:57.500 --> 13:58.333
all on your own.

13:58.333 --> 13:59.033
(stammers)

13:59.033 --> 14:00.466
Uh, d...

14:01.633 --> 14:02.633
(boxes clatter)

14:04.033 --> 14:05.666
Erica, what are
you doing?

14:05.666 --> 14:09.100
Um...

14:09.100 --> 14:10.100
Tissue?

14:11.666 --> 14:14.100
Woman: (singing)
♪ To open up my voice ♪

14:14.100 --> 14:18.133
♪ And let myself sing
the way I know I can ♪

14:19.166 --> 14:22.066
♪ I gotta get my soul free ♪

14:23.066 --> 14:26.033
♪ It's not the same
for all of us ♪

14:26.033 --> 14:27.066
(sighs heavily)

14:27.066 --> 14:28.600
♪ To let my feet... ♪

14:28.600 --> 14:30.333
Thank you.

14:30.333 --> 14:33.200
For not rubbing it
in my face.

14:33.200 --> 14:34.600
You were right
all along and...

14:34.600 --> 14:35.433
(sigh of disgust)

14:35.433 --> 14:37.100
I was so
awful to you.

14:37.100 --> 14:38.533
No, Sam,

14:38.533 --> 14:40.766
don't even worry
about that.

14:40.766 --> 14:44.266
Look, I'm just really
proud of you,

14:44.266 --> 14:47.533
and I can't even imagine
how hard this is.

14:47.533 --> 14:49.700
Kai: Next up, a fine
bottle of Gamay.

14:49.700 --> 14:51.566
It's got a cat
on the label,

14:51.566 --> 14:53.366
so you know
it's the good stuff.

14:53.366 --> 14:56.066
Sam and Erica:
(chuckle politely)

14:56.300 --> 14:58.166
Oh, Erica,
you're exhausted.

14:58.166 --> 14:59.100
Mm-mm.

14:59.100 --> 15:00.400
I show up on
your doorstep,

15:00.400 --> 15:02.766
and interrupt your work,
and your romantic evening.

15:02.766 --> 15:05.200
Mm, no romantic
evening.

15:05.200 --> 15:06.533
No?

15:06.533 --> 15:08.400
Okay, you should have seen
what Ethan wasn't wearing

15:08.400 --> 15:10.266
when I showed up.

15:10.266 --> 15:11.233
Really?!

15:11.233 --> 15:12.500
Yeah.

15:13.266 --> 15:16.500
Things have been...
A little awkward between us.

15:16.500 --> 15:18.000
Then you should
go home.

15:18.000 --> 15:20.033
I'm not gonna abandon
you in a bar.

15:20.033 --> 15:22.300
Erica, you have done
enough for me.

15:22.300 --> 15:24.600
If there's something
going on there with Ethan,

15:24.600 --> 15:25.733
go fix it.

15:25.733 --> 15:29.533
No, really, you know,
it's no big thing.

15:29.533 --> 15:32.333
It never is
at the start.

15:32.333 --> 15:35.066
Kai: Hey, part of my
job description's

15:35.066 --> 15:36.133
showing the
broken-hearted

15:36.133 --> 15:39.133
how the goblins staff
likes to party.

15:39.133 --> 15:41.700
I... I don't think
that Sam is in any state

15:41.700 --> 15:43.666
to keep up
with you, Kai.

15:43.666 --> 15:45.333
Sam: Erica,
just go.

15:46.333 --> 15:47.533
And don't
wait up.

15:47.533 --> 15:49.233
I won't.

15:49.233 --> 15:50.033
Thank you.

15:50.033 --> 15:51.033
There you go.

15:51.033 --> 15:52.066
I'll be fine.

15:52.066 --> 15:53.400
Okay.

15:53.400 --> 15:55.066
Call any time.

15:56.066 --> 15:58.300
So what, you don't trust
me with your sister?

16:00.166 --> 16:01.533
Look, it's just...

16:01.533 --> 16:05.133
I mean, Sam, she's really
fragile right now.

16:05.133 --> 16:08.500
Look, just...
Don't let her get drunk,

16:08.500 --> 16:10.333
and keep the
gross guys away.

16:10.333 --> 16:12.100
Just please take
care of her.

16:12.100 --> 16:13.333
She'll be fine.

16:13.333 --> 16:14.600
Really.

16:14.600 --> 16:15.600
Go.

16:17.066 --> 16:19.233
Okay. Good night.
Thank you.

16:19.233 --> 16:20.233
Good night.

16:23.233 --> 16:25.033
(elevator dings open)

16:35.233 --> 16:37.166
Jules.

16:37.166 --> 16:38.400
Thomas.

16:38.400 --> 16:40.266
Please take
a seat.

16:40.466 --> 16:42.500
I kinda feel like
I've been sent down

16:42.500 --> 16:44.433
to the principal's
office.

16:44.433 --> 16:46.300
Like you're gonna pull
out your yardstick

16:46.300 --> 16:48.466
and spank me.

16:49.533 --> 16:52.266
I'm gonna just cut
to the chase.

16:52.266 --> 16:54.733
I think we both know
that we work well together.

16:54.733 --> 16:56.666
As lovers?

16:56.666 --> 16:58.600
But the past
is the past

16:58.600 --> 17:01.333
and I am willing
to move on.

17:01.333 --> 17:03.366
Focus, as you would
say, on the now.

17:03.366 --> 17:06.700
Mm, so, we just pretend
like it never happened?

17:06.700 --> 17:09.133
We pretend like you
didn't rip my balls off

17:09.133 --> 17:10.766
in front of your
entire staff?

17:10.766 --> 17:13.466
Yes, and we pretend you
didn't go behind my back,

17:13.466 --> 17:15.466
like a weasel,
to Scott Galvin.

17:15.466 --> 17:17.099
Not to mention
Meeri.

17:17.099 --> 17:18.099
And that's it?

17:18.099 --> 17:19.099
That's it.

17:20.633 --> 17:21.633
Deal.

17:25.466 --> 17:27.033
Oh.

17:27.033 --> 17:29.466
Provided I get
one thing.

17:29.466 --> 17:31.466
What's that,
your typeface?

17:31.466 --> 17:32.666
No.

17:32.666 --> 17:35.400
I want an apology
from you.

17:36.400 --> 17:37.200
For what?

17:37.200 --> 17:39.266
For disrespecting me,

17:39.266 --> 17:41.333
for wounding
my male pride.

17:41.333 --> 17:43.433
Hell, just for
the fun of it.

17:43.433 --> 17:45.633
And I want you to
beg for forgiveness

17:45.633 --> 17:48.300
in front of everyone.

17:48.300 --> 17:50.400
You show me the
respect I deserve,

17:50.400 --> 17:52.466
and you can keep
riding my coattails.

17:52.466 --> 17:53.166
Don't,

17:53.166 --> 17:54.100
(inhales)

17:54.100 --> 17:56.400
and some other
vampire will.

18:09.466 --> 18:10.466
Hey.

18:10.466 --> 18:11.400
Hey. I, uh,

18:11.400 --> 18:13.133
I made up the
couch for Sam.

18:13.133 --> 18:14.133
Oh, thank you.

18:15.233 --> 18:17.000
So, how is she?

18:17.000 --> 18:18.666
You know what,
she's...

18:18.666 --> 18:20.000
Better.

18:20.000 --> 18:22.233
All things considered.

18:22.233 --> 18:23.533
So...

18:23.533 --> 18:25.533
Sam said she found
you half-naked,

18:25.533 --> 18:27.066
lighting candles.

18:27.066 --> 18:29.133
Well, if your sister wasn't
having a marital crisis,

18:29.133 --> 18:31.733
you could've spent the evening
with me as your slave.

18:33.166 --> 18:34.166
Really?

18:38.166 --> 18:40.566
Is that what
you'd like?

18:40.566 --> 18:43.166
Oh, um, if you would.
I mean, sure.

18:43.166 --> 18:45.200
We could take out
a bottle of wine

18:45.200 --> 18:47.333
and have a bath.

18:47.333 --> 18:49.066
We could, or...

18:51.300 --> 18:52.300
(exhales)

18:54.566 --> 18:56.566
You could
show me.

18:59.700 --> 19:00.433
(uncomfortable)

19:00.433 --> 19:01.300
No.

19:01.300 --> 19:02.433
Why?

19:02.433 --> 19:05.033
Because that would
just be weird.

19:05.033 --> 19:08.133
Or it could be
really hot, Ethan.

19:09.133 --> 19:10.133
Please?

19:11.733 --> 19:13.200
Please?

19:13.200 --> 19:16.300
Woman: (singing)
♪ Takes me a night ♪

19:17.300 --> 19:20.733
♪ To look in your eyes ♪

19:21.733 --> 19:25.333
♪ The wind on my face ♪

19:26.333 --> 19:29.700
♪ The jewels in the sky ♪

19:30.700 --> 19:34.066
♪ I deeply breathe ♪

19:35.066 --> 19:38.000
♪ The forest air ♪

19:39.000 --> 19:42.300
♪ And I sigh ♪

19:42.300 --> 19:45.300
♪ I've fallen in love ♪

19:48.266 --> 19:50.466
♪ Again ♪

19:51.500 --> 19:53.633
♪ Open your arms ♪

19:55.633 --> 19:58.033
♪ He carried me far ♪

20:00.033 --> 20:03.500
♪ I'll give you my heart ♪
(give you my skin)

20:04.500 --> 20:06.366
♪ Give you my skin ♪

20:10.533 --> 20:12.133
♪ Whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa ♪

20:12.133 --> 20:19.266
♪

20:19.266 --> 20:21.333
♪ Whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa ♪

20:24.400 --> 20:25.400
You know what, dude?

20:25.400 --> 20:27.100
Getting on a plane
like that,

20:27.100 --> 20:29.166
not even your
toothbrush?

20:29.166 --> 20:30.533
That takes guts.

20:30.533 --> 20:31.633
Yeah.

20:31.633 --> 20:34.133
And you make it
sound almost cool.

20:34.133 --> 20:35.400
It is cool.

20:37.100 --> 20:40.533
Ah, I know how hard it is
to throw everything away

20:40.533 --> 20:42.300
and start over.

20:43.466 --> 20:45.733
You have beautiful eyes.

20:46.733 --> 20:49.033
I'm sorry,
I'm so bad at this.

20:49.033 --> 20:50.300
No, you're not,
believe me.

20:50.300 --> 20:53.600
It doesn't hurt
that you're beautiful.

20:53.600 --> 20:56.300
But I promised your sister
I'd take care of you.

21:00.066 --> 21:05.033
♪ The city seems so far ♪

21:09.200 --> 21:12.533
♪ Don't ever leave ♪
(you are my...)

21:13.533 --> 21:15.166
♪ You are my heart ♪

21:15.166 --> 21:16.366
Nurse: (video plays)
what's up?

21:16.366 --> 21:17.566
Doctor: Hey,
um, I'm just...

21:17.566 --> 21:18.766
Nurse: Is there
a problem?

21:18.766 --> 21:20.366
Doctor: Yeah, there's
a big problem.

21:20.366 --> 21:23.333
You know, if things don't
add up and look right,

21:23.333 --> 21:25.733
then I'm gonna... I'm
gonna be out of a job.

21:25.733 --> 21:27.533
You're gonna be
out of a job!

21:27.533 --> 21:30.166
If I lose funding,
we're both out of a job!

21:30.166 --> 21:32.333
Wow, this guy's really
concerned about his job.

21:32.333 --> 21:33.600
Nurse: Are you really...

21:33.600 --> 21:36.166
Doctor: Come on, in this
economy, we need our jobs.

21:36.166 --> 21:38.266
I mean, who writes
this stuff?

21:38.266 --> 21:40.566
I'm pretty sure
they make it up.

21:40.566 --> 21:42.066
Oh, right.

21:42.066 --> 21:44.100
I've got things
that I gotta get done

21:44.100 --> 21:46.300
or we're both gonna
be out of a job.

21:46.300 --> 21:48.633
Ah, don't worry,
I'm here.

21:49.266 --> 21:50.600
I will make
you happy.

21:50.600 --> 21:52.133
(stifles a laugh)

21:52.133 --> 21:53.333
Doctor: Thi...this... This
kind of inappropriate.

21:53.333 --> 21:55.600
I've got things to do
I gotta get done.

21:55.600 --> 21:57.000
I'm gonna lose
funding...

21:57.000 --> 21:58.100
(laughing)

21:58.100 --> 21:59.433
Doctor: No, it's not
working if i...

21:59.433 --> 22:02.466
If we don't get the funding
then I'm out of a job,

22:02.466 --> 22:03.666
you're out of a job,

22:03.666 --> 22:05.033
(Erica laughs)

22:05.033 --> 22:06.266
And we're gonna be
stuck on the street.

22:06.266 --> 22:08.066
Nurse: No, don't
worry, I am here.

22:08.066 --> 22:08.666
Sorry.

22:08.666 --> 22:09.433
Nurse: Are
you busy?

22:09.433 --> 22:10.266
Doctor:
Well, I was.

22:10.266 --> 22:11.333
(laughing)

22:11.333 --> 22:12.533
Doctor: I was trying
to get something done.

22:12.533 --> 22:13.533
(snorts)

22:17.766 --> 22:19.100
(clears throat)

22:19.100 --> 22:21.100
Okay, this is stupid.
I'm gonna go to bed.

22:21.100 --> 22:22.166
No, no, I didn't...

22:22.166 --> 22:24.400
Look, I didn't mean
to make fun at all.

22:24.400 --> 22:26.466
I won't. I'll stop.

22:33.000 --> 22:35.100
(clears throat)

22:35.100 --> 22:36.166
Nurse:
(moans loudly)

22:36.166 --> 22:37.300
Oh my god.

22:37.300 --> 22:39.000
Okay.

22:39.000 --> 22:40.700
No, wait-wait-wait-
wait-wait-wait.

22:40.700 --> 22:42.533
Erica, please,
can we just drop it?

22:42.533 --> 22:44.566
Look, Ethan,
I'm just, I'm just...

22:44.566 --> 22:49.300
I'm trying to understand,
you know, what you like.

22:51.266 --> 22:52.766
I have an idea.

22:53.766 --> 22:55.166
Just...

22:56.166 --> 22:57.733
Just...

22:57.733 --> 22:59.100
Trust me.

22:59.100 --> 23:09.133
♪

23:09.133 --> 23:31.266
♪

23:31.266 --> 23:32.266
(knocking)

23:37.000 --> 23:38.033
(Russian accent)

23:38.033 --> 23:42.400
Doctor, did you, did
you call for me?

23:42.400 --> 23:43.400
Erica...

23:43.400 --> 23:44.400
Shhh!

23:45.700 --> 23:47.666
Doctor Wakefield,

23:48.566 --> 23:51.433
do you need me
to assist you

23:52.733 --> 23:55.000
with your research?

23:57.400 --> 23:59.533
I, uh... I guess so.

24:02.466 --> 24:03.766
Um, Erica,
can we just...

24:03.766 --> 24:04.766
Shhh!

24:06.766 --> 24:09.366
My name is, uh,
Nurse Stran...

24:10.366 --> 24:11.366
Nurse Straddle.

24:24.500 --> 24:26.566
Really, Erica,
you don't have to.

24:26.566 --> 24:28.566
Oh, but I want to.

24:30.233 --> 24:31.733
Why? Are you...

24:32.733 --> 24:34.700
Are you busy?

24:36.433 --> 24:39.600
Are you worried
about your job?

24:46.100 --> 24:47.500
Ethan: Uh, really,
uh, don't.

24:47.500 --> 24:50.266
Let's just stop
this, okay?

24:53.233 --> 24:54.066
(stammers)

24:54.066 --> 24:56.233
I just thought
that...

24:56.233 --> 24:59.100
That it might
be fun and...

24:59.100 --> 25:01.366
And that it would
help you.

25:01.366 --> 25:04.366
I don't need help
to want you.

25:07.700 --> 25:08.733
Uh, you're
absolutely right,

25:08.733 --> 25:12.133
it looks much better
on the computer.

25:13.300 --> 25:22.766
♪

25:22.766 --> 25:23.766
(sighs heavily)

25:42.533 --> 25:44.566
(door opens
and shuts)

25:59.066 --> 26:00.066
(cups clatter)

26:06.566 --> 26:07.600
(metallic clang)

26:07.600 --> 26:10.300
Dr. Fred:
Big night last night?

26:10.300 --> 26:13.166
Can't hear you over the blood
pounding in my ears.

26:13.166 --> 26:16.700
Mm, reminds me
of your rock'n'roll days.

26:16.700 --> 26:18.566
God, those were
fun times.

26:18.566 --> 26:22.366
You know, you really oughta
take that biscotti to go,

26:22.366 --> 26:23.466
Dr. Fred.

26:24.766 --> 26:27.700
You can try to rewrite
who you are.

26:27.700 --> 26:30.500
But the guy from 2019?

26:30.500 --> 26:33.000
He's right here
in front of me,

26:33.000 --> 26:35.000
and he was in full form
last night.

26:44.700 --> 26:46.500
I think we should
start the book

26:46.500 --> 26:47.700
with a more
shocking chapter,

26:47.700 --> 26:49.533
something to, you
know, reel them in.

26:49.533 --> 26:50.766
Hmm, I guess, but...

26:50.766 --> 26:52.633
Alexis:
What if we start with...

26:52.633 --> 26:53.666
Self-pleasuring.

26:53.666 --> 26:55.466
Learn how to make
yourself happy

26:55.466 --> 26:59.100
before you worry
about anyone else.

26:59.100 --> 27:02.066
Your friend might find
that interesting, yes?

27:02.066 --> 27:03.500
I bet she would.

27:03.500 --> 27:05.100
It would help her
to understand

27:05.100 --> 27:08.100
that we all have needs
we don't like to talk about.

27:08.100 --> 27:10.066
I think that
she gets that.

27:10.066 --> 27:11.066
Does she?

27:11.066 --> 27:12.200
Yes, and I...

27:12.200 --> 27:13.100
(stammering)

27:13.100 --> 27:14.100
I bet that she
would argue

27:14.100 --> 27:15.733
that he's the
one with the issues.

27:15.733 --> 27:17.433
How so?

27:17.433 --> 27:18.633
Well, she...

27:18.633 --> 27:22.500
I mean, she keeps trying
to understand his needs

27:22.500 --> 27:24.766
and to give him
what he wants.

27:24.766 --> 27:28.066
Uh, what about
what she wants?

27:28.066 --> 27:29.633
Has she told him?

27:29.633 --> 27:32.433
Does she even
know herself?

27:40.666 --> 27:42.266
(knocking on door)

27:49.700 --> 27:50.700
Hey, Sam.

27:52.333 --> 27:55.400
You got coffee
and, uh, a vase?

28:00.233 --> 28:01.533
Of course I
was scared.

28:01.533 --> 28:03.566
I came home from work,
you weren't there,

28:03.566 --> 28:06.166
there was no note,
there was no warning.

28:06.166 --> 28:07.700
And that took you
how long?

28:07.700 --> 28:09.033
To notice, I mean.

28:09.033 --> 28:11.466
'cause the night before,
I was gone for hours

28:11.466 --> 28:13.000
and you just...

28:13.000 --> 28:14.500
Sam, I got on
an airplane.

28:14.500 --> 28:15.600
I got here,

28:15.600 --> 28:17.700
I got to you as fast
as I physically could,

28:17.700 --> 28:19.600
so, yeah, yeah,
I noticed.

28:19.600 --> 28:23.133
Just come back
with me, please?

28:23.133 --> 28:25.700
I screwed up,
I know it.

28:25.700 --> 28:28.366
London was supposed to be
our chance to break free

28:28.366 --> 28:30.433
from all the bullshit.

28:30.433 --> 28:32.433
I fulfilled my end
of the bargain.

28:32.433 --> 28:34.166
I know you did.

28:34.166 --> 28:36.366
But... I didn't.

28:36.366 --> 28:38.366
There's no excuse.

28:41.166 --> 28:43.300
Look, I'm not
a saint, okay?

28:43.300 --> 28:46.466
I-I-I messed up
and I admit that,

28:46.466 --> 28:49.100
but I wanna
work on it.

28:49.100 --> 28:50.766
I need you, Sam.

28:56.600 --> 28:58.200
(door clicks open)

29:00.333 --> 29:01.333
Hey.

29:01.333 --> 29:02.333
Hey.

29:03.466 --> 29:04.733
Where's Sam?

29:04.733 --> 29:06.200
Erica: Um, I
don't know,

29:06.200 --> 29:08.200
she wasn't here
when I got home.

29:09.200 --> 29:12.500
So, do you wanna talk
now, about last night?

29:14.333 --> 29:17.500
I dunno. I'm starting to think
that talking is overrated.

29:17.500 --> 29:19.366
My best guess is
that you're upset

29:19.366 --> 29:21.333
about walking
in and...

29:21.333 --> 29:23.033
Seeing me...

29:23.033 --> 29:25.466
(sighs)

29:25.466 --> 29:27.200
Erica...

29:28.333 --> 29:29.600
Yes. okay?

29:31.066 --> 29:32.266
A little.

29:33.033 --> 29:34.633
And it wasn't that
you were doing

29:34.633 --> 29:36.066
what you
were doing.

29:36.066 --> 29:37.266
It's just...

29:37.633 --> 29:39.766
Watching you,
it was like...

29:39.766 --> 29:43.066
Seeing this different
part of you and...

29:43.066 --> 29:45.633
That made me
realize that...

29:45.633 --> 29:46.633
There's stuff
about me

29:46.633 --> 29:49.766
